The article is a press gaggle by Principal Deputy Press Secretary Eric Schultz during a flight from Oklahoma to Andrews Air Force Base. Schultz announces that President Obama will travel to Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania, to address the Veterans of Foreign Wars National Convention on July 21st. He also discusses the President's response to the shootings in Chattanooga and Prime Minister Cameron's plans to open a British embassy in Tehran. Schultz addresses criticisms of the administration's handling of the Iran deal and discusses the outreach efforts being made to Congress. He also mentions the President's focus on criminal justice reform and his recent visit to a federal prison. Schultz briefly mentions the President's remarks on Bill Cosby and the Medal of Freedom, as well as the Greek austerity measures and the Confederate flag.